The 'kindred' is not easy to trace: but on
John xix, 25, some take <i>his mother's sister</i> to be <i>the
mother of the sons of Zebedee</i> of Matt. xxvii, 56, i.e.,
<i>Salome</i>, Mark xv, 40. If there was not kindred, there
was certainly friendship, which is enough for the
argument.


